&quot;Dante, get off me,&quot; groaned Dahnyella as she tried to force him off.<br>
<br>
She could feel herself being freed of Dante's weight as he rolled off of her. Forcing herself to her feet, she had a feeling they weren't in Nektulos Forest any more.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where are we?&quot; came Telus' voice from a few feet away.<br>
<br>
As Dahnyella tried to cast her senses out, Dante came and stood by her side. A cold chill ran down her spine as his energy joined her own, but it quickly subsided as her senses kicked in. She could taste death, and touch stone, moss covered at that. Her eyes tingled as she slipped into a new dimension, a castle. &quot;We're in a courtyard,&quot; Dahnyella stated bluntly as her eyes rolled open.<br>
<br>
Telus nodded and helped his sister, Bellona, to her feet<br>
<br>
&quot;Can you pin point the location, Ella?&quot; Bellona enquired<br>
<br>
Dahnyella shook her head and pointed to her ear, &quot;Spires are near, they're clouding my senses.&quot;<br>
<br>
Bellona looked at her and arched an eyebrow, /How far off are the spires?/<br>
<br>
/Just a couple of miles, Bellie./<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's roll-&quot;<br>
<br>
Screams cut Bellona's order off. It was Malasu.<br>
<br>
&quot;I swear to Bristlebane, that Paladin will cost us our lives,&quot; exclaimed Dahnyella, as she rooted Malasu's attacker. Closing her eyes, Dahnyella drew invisibility sigils in the air, then went off to save Malasu.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dahnyella-&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;She'll be fine, Dante,&quot; said Telus grinning as lightning conquered the sky.<br>
<br>
Dahnyella came back with Malasu by the ear, &quot;... don't understand you...&quot; Pushing Malasu into the group, she fancied a glare. Flipping her chesnut hair over her shoulder, she sighed, &quot;Now, I'd like to know how we got here.&quot; When her words finished she shot one final glare at Malasu.<br>
<br>
Dante helped Malasu to balance as Dahnyella, Telus, and Bellona discussed the portal they had stumbled upon in the middle of Nektulos Forest. &quot;How else would we have practically fallen from the sky,&quot; added Telus.<br>
<br>
Dahnyella shivered as Dante came up behind her and slowly leaned in toward her neck. Bellona shook her head, and he pulled away. She was used to his vampiric urges, and she was beginning to get used to fear's finger tips running down her back everytime her came near.<br>
<br>
Malasu glared at Dahnyella and Dante, with hurt laced in her eyes. Dahnyella could have cared less.<br>
<br>
&quot;Guys...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What Telus?&quot; asked Bellona engulfed in a map.<br>
<br>
Telus gulped, glancing around, &quot;We have company.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dahnyella looked around as Dante pressed a hand to the small of her back, and reached out a hand to Malasu. They were every where, their red eyes blazing out of the brush. She glanced at Telus and Bellona, then grinning closed her eyes.<br>
<br>
As Dahnyella's eyes rolled open a fog encased them all. Her power chant drifted over the smoke colored mist, transforming it into a crimson light. Bellona and Telus added to the sphere of power, as Dante and Malasu followed suit.<br>
<br>
&quot;On my count release the energies,&quot; Dahnyella breathed, &quot;1... 2... 3... NOW!&quot;<br>
<br>
A cone of white light shot up through the sphere sending a wave of destructive power over a 5 mile radius.<br>
<br>
As the ground began to rumble, and their surroundings took fire, they stood. Each of them could feel their God standing by them at that moment. <br>
<br>
As they all opened their eyes, they could see what they had done. Before them lay a land in ruins, smoke rolling off of charcoal tree stumps, a toppled castle a mile or so off, and dead bodies every where. Yet, all they cared for at that moment were the Nexus Spires. Right there before them, a clear shot.<br>
<br>
Bellona smiled, &quot;You never cease to amaze me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Dahnyella took a bow, then indicated the portal, &quot;Shall we?&quot;<br>
<br>
Bellona took Telus' arm, as Dahnyella took to their side twirling her staff. Dante and Malasu followed closely behind them, Malasu leaned on his shoulder, but at that moment he seemed to care not. They all seemed to take in the ruins... the destruction they cause when together. <p><HTML>
